    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>July 11/51</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>. Dr Sir. Yr favor of <date>7th</date> is<lb/> at
                hand. I am straightening up what<lb/> is crooked here, among yr subscribers,
                and<lb/> we shall progress smoothly hereafter. I<lb/> have 2 new subscribers for
                you</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>I. L. Falk &amp; Co</persName> — <placeName>Charleston S.
                    C.</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>L H Joseph</persName> — care <persName>Carson Harlee &amp;
                    Co</persName><lb/>
                <placeName>Charleston S. C.</placeName></p>
            <p>and a prospect of some others. <persName>Messrs<lb/> Joseph &amp; Falk</persName>
                desire to begin with the<lb/>
                <date>July</date> or <date>August</date> number &amp; not from the<lb/> beginning of
                the volume. Among those<lb/> to whom you sent the Occident (<hi rend="underline"
                    >not</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">subscribers</hi>) the following I have<lb/> prevailed upon to
                keep &amp; subscribe</p>
            <table cols="2" rows="2">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>P Wineman</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Isaac Harris</persName>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Chas H Levy</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>B Mordecai</persName>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p>&amp; these named below decline keeping<lb/>it.</p>
            <table cols="2" rows="4">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>J J Cohen</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>M Jacobs</persName>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>I L DeLange</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Mrs M L Cohen</persName>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Leopold Cohn</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>B D Lazarus</persName>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>C H Moise</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell/>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p>I have not been able to get but<lb/> a few of the numbers from the last<lb/> named,
                and they do not trouble<lb/> themselves to hunt them up, as they<lb/> contend that
                being sent without</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>their authority they are not bound to<lb/> look up and restore them. <persName>D C
                    Seixas</persName><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">subscribed through me</hi> and I shall<lb/> see him to day—if
                he chooses to<lb/> send his Occident back he may<lb/> do so but he is <hi
                    rend="underline">bound to pay</hi> and<lb/> I shall collect the money if
                possible.<lb/> The best course My dear Sir is to<lb/> send to <hi rend="underline"
                    >subscribers</hi> only, for the folks<lb/> here are not any too scrupulous
                in<lb/> certain matters, and will read yr<lb/> magazine without intending to
                pay<lb/> Suppose you take the enclosed<lb/> list and make up yr mail by<lb/> it. I
                think it is correct.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I would send you the $9 collected<lb/> from <persName>A
                    Moise</persName> soon, but am waiting<lb/> for <persName>Mrs
                    Griswolds</persName> money to accomp<lb/>-any it. <persName>Mrs G</persName> is
                out of the city &amp;<lb/> I believe has gone <placeName>North</placeName>. When
                I<lb/> sent they were all out at her house<lb/> but said if I sent again perhaps<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs Myers</persName> (her Aunt) would pay<lb/> the bill. This I intend to
                do.</p>
            <p>Your last Occident has given<lb/> some offense here in consequence<lb/> of the
                articles vs<add>?</add>
                <persName>Posnanski</persName> which<lb/> appeared therein. I do not doubt</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>that <persName>D C Seixas</persName> returned his number<lb/> on that account.
                However, all you<lb/> lose (if lose you do) I will try<lb/> and make up.</p>
            <p>Indeed, although the few irreligious<lb/> and prejudiced men who still rally<lb/>
                around <persName>Mr Posnanski</persName> may be<lb/> discontented with you for a
                time,<lb/> yet as yr course is eminently<lb/> correct &amp; <hi rend="underline"
                    >Judaistic</hi>, justice will be<lb/> done you in the end.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am much hurried and<lb/> must close. Believe me</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Truly Yrs</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">Thos J Moise</persName>
            </p>
            <p>I will try &amp; collect<lb/> up some of the<lb/> numbers &amp; send them<lb/> on by
                private hand</p>
        </body>
